songs.title: The One
songs.lyrics:
[Snippet]

[Intro]
Baby, baby, baby

[Verse 1]
Baby, I thought it was over, thought it was over
But you makin' me question my motives, question my motives
Yeah, you can feel the emotions, feel the emotions
Yeah, how did I do it I, baby girl, I just don't know how to show, know how to show it

[Chorus]
Got me feeling some kind of season
But baby, I been dreamin' 'bout leavin'
But now that I been dreamin' 'bout breathin'
You could be the one, you could be the one

[Post-Chorus]
You could be the one, you could be the one
You could be the one, you could be the one
You could be the one, you could be the one
You could be the one, you could be the one

[Verse 2]
Man this is difficult, man this is difficult
I ain't gonna lie to you baby 'cause I'm really into you
I'm really into you but I know
We should be friends, we should be friends
Maybe this talking and texting is
Up late on the phone, it's just gotta end

[Bridge]
God, don't you know, don't you know
Don't you know, don't you know
Look what you've done to me, look what you've done to me
I can't help but feel like you might be the one-
